  "local_port": 49760,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How do I change gender in booked IRCTC e-tickets?",
  "response": "To change the gender on booked IRCTC e-tickets, you'll need to follow these steps:\n\n1. **Contact IRCTC Customer Care:**\n   - The first step is to reach out to IRCTC's customer care. You can do this by calling their toll-free number 1800-111-139 or by emailing them at care@irctc.co.in.\n   - Explain your situation clearly and provide your PNR number.\n\n2. **Visit the Nearest Reservation Office:**\n   - If the customer care advises, you may need to visit the nearest railway reservation office or a PRS (Passenger Reservation System) counter.\n   - Carry a valid government-issued ID proof that reflects your correct gender.\n\n3. **Submit a Written Request:**\n   - At the reservation office, you'll need to submit a written request for changing the gender on your ticket.\n   - Include your PNR number and attach a photocopy of your ID proof.\n\n4. **Wait for Confirmation:**\n   - The railway authorities will review your request. If approved, they will make the necessary changes to your e-ticket.\n   - You'll receive a confirmation via email or SMS once the changes are processed.\n\n5. **Check Your Updated Ticket:**\n   - Once you receive the confirmation, log into your IRCTC account and check your e-ticket to ensure the gender has been updated correctly.\n\n**Important Notes:**\n- Changes to gender on e-tickets can only be made before the chart is prepared, which is usually 4 hours before the train's departure.\n- The process may vary slightly depending on specific circumstances and the discretion of the railway authorities.\n- It's advisable to make such requests as early as possible to avoid any last-minute hassles.\n\nBy following these steps, you should be able to change the gender on your booked IRCTC e-tickets. If you encounter any issues, don't hesitate to seek further assistance from IRCTC customer care.",
